<PLACE><ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Cattaraugus</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">New York</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">United States</ENAMEX></PLACE>
<SBODY>1 5 4
WARRANTY <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">DEED</ENAMEX>.
This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Twenty Third day of April
of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and Eighty one</TIMEX> Between <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah Donovan</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Jeremiah S
Donovan</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Olean</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Cattaraugus County</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">New York</ENAMEX>.
of the first part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">George E. Rawaly</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Chester A Tousey</ENAMEX> of the same place.
of the second part,
Witnesseth, That the said parties of the first part, in consideration of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">Two Thousand three hundred and sixty six Dollars</NUMEX>,
( <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$23660</NUMEX>)
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">them</ENAMEX> duly paid, have sold, and by these Presents do grant and convey to the said parties of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>,
ALL THAT <ENAMEX TYPE="VEHICLE">TRACTOR</ENAMEX> PARCEL OF LAND, situate in the ⌨own of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Olean</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Cattaraugus</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State
of New York</ENAMEX> and which on a map or survey of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Olean</ENAMEX> made by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Jef. Gosseline</ENAMEX> is
bounded and described as follows: Commencing at the south east corner of lot number
three in Block number fifty; thence north <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">five</NUMEX> Chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">fifty eight</NUMEX> links to the south
east corner of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Leonard</ENAMEX> Lays land thence west <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">twelve</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">eleven</NUMEX> links to the center of
<ENAMEX TYPE="STRUCTURE">Thirteenth Street</ENAMEX>, thence south on the center of <ENAMEX TYPE="STRUCTURE">thirteenth street</ENAMEX> <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">five</NUMEX> chains and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">fifty eight</NUMEX>
links to the south west corner of lot number three in Block number forty eight thence
east <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">twelve</NUMEX> chains and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">eleven</NUMEX> links to the place of beginning, containing <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">six</NUMEX> acres and
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">about seventy six hundredths</NUMEX> acres, more or less. ( it being distinctly and explicitty understood
that the said <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">grantees</ENAMEX> pay at the rate of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$350</NUMEX> an acre for said premises and no more)
With the appurtenances, and all the Estate, Title and Interest therein of the said parties of the first part. And the said parties
for <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah Donovan</ENAMEX> one of said parties) of the first part,
do hereby covenant and agree to and with the said parties of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, that at the time of the ensealing
and delivery of these presents, said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah</ENAMEX> is the lawful owner and that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">she</ENAMEX> is well seized of the premises above
conveyed, free and clear from all incumbrances of every name and nature, legal or equitable and
that the premises thus conveyed, in the quiet and peaceable possession of the said parties of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX>
will forever WARRANT AND DEFEND against any person <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">whomsoever</ENAMEX> lawfully claiming the same or any part thereof.
In Witness Whereof. The parties of the first part have hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> hand and seal the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
Sealed and Delivered in Presence of
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah ⌨⌨ Donovan</ENAMEX> ( L.S)
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">D.H. Bolles</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Jeremiah</ENAMEX> ⌨⌨ <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Donovan</ENAMEX>
[ L. S.]
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">STATE OF NEW YORK</ENAMEX>.
County of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">CATTARAUGUS</ENAMEX> 5 s. on the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">23rd
day of April
in the year one thousand eight hundred and
Eighty One</TIMEX> before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, the subscriber, personally appeared <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah Down</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Jeremiah Donovan</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Olean</ENAMEX> in
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> known to be the same person described in and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the within
and <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">mother</ENAMEX> and an alknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX> scouted the same on a private examination by <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, apart from <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX>, acknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">she</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">he</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX>,
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">A.T. Eaton</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Notary Public</ENAMEX>.
████████ ▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓
</SBODY>
</NBX>

of the second part,

to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">them</ENAMEX> duly paid, have sold, and by these Presents do grant and convey to the said parties of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>,

east <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">twelve</NUMEX> chains and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">eleven</NUMEX> links to the place of beginning, containing <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">six</NUMEX> acres and
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">about seventy six hundredths</NUMEX> acres, more or less. ( it being distinctly and explicitty understood

With the appurtenances, and all the Estate, Title and Interest therein of the said parties of the first part. And the said parties
for <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah Donovan</ENAMEX> one of said parties) of the first part,

<SBODY>1 5 4
WARRANTY <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">DEED</ENAMEX>.
This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Twenty Third day of April
of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and Eighty one</TIMEX> Between <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah Donovan</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Jeremiah S
Donovan</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Olean</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Cattaraugus County</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">New York</ENAMEX>.
of the first part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">George E. Rawaly</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Chester A Tousey</ENAMEX> of the same place.
of the second part,
Witnesseth, That the said parties of the first part, in consideration of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">Two Thousand three hundred and sixty six Dollars</NUMEX>,
( <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$23660</NUMEX>)
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">them</ENAMEX> duly paid, have sold, and by these Presents do grant and convey to the said parties of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>,
ALL THAT <ENAMEX TYPE="VEHICLE">TRACTOR</ENAMEX> PARCEL OF LAND, situate in the ⌨own of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Olean</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Cattaraugus</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State
of New York</ENAMEX> and which on a map or survey of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Olean</ENAMEX> made by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Jef. Gosseline</ENAMEX> is
bounded and described as follows: Commencing at the south east corner of lot number
three in Block number fifty; thence north <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">five</NUMEX> Chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">fifty eight</NUMEX> links to the south
east corner of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Leonard</ENAMEX> Lays land thence west <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">twelve</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">eleven</NUMEX> links to the center of
<ENAMEX TYPE="STRUCTURE">Thirteenth Street</ENAMEX>, thence south on the center of <ENAMEX TYPE="STRUCTURE">thirteenth street</ENAMEX> <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">five</NUMEX> chains and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">fifty eight</NUMEX>
links to the south west corner of lot number three in Block number forty eight thence
east <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">twelve</NUMEX> chains and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">eleven</NUMEX> links to the place of beginning, containing <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">six</NUMEX> acres and
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">about seventy six hundredths</NUMEX> acres, more or less. ( it being distinctly and explicitty understood
that the said <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">grantees</ENAMEX> pay at the rate of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$350</NUMEX> an acre for said premises and no more)
With the appurtenances, and all the Estate, Title and Interest therein of the said parties of the first part. And the said parties
for <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah Donovan</ENAMEX> one of said parties) of the first part,
do hereby covenant and agree to and with the said parties of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, that at the time of the ensealing
and delivery of these presents, said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah</ENAMEX> is the lawful owner and that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">she</ENAMEX> is well seized of the premises above
conveyed, free and clear from all incumbrances of every name and nature, legal or equitable and
that the premises thus conveyed, in the quiet and peaceable possession of the said parties of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX>
will forever WARRANT AND DEFEND against any person <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">whomsoever</ENAMEX> lawfully claiming the same or any part thereof.
In Witness Whereof. The parties of the first part have hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> hand and seal the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
Sealed and Delivered in Presence of
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah ⌨⌨ Donovan</ENAMEX> ( L.S)
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">D.H. Bolles</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Jeremiah</ENAMEX> ⌨⌨ <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Donovan</ENAMEX>
[ L. S.]
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">STATE OF NEW YORK</ENAMEX>.
County of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">CATTARAUGUS</ENAMEX> 5 s. on the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">23rd
day of April
in the year one thousand eight hundred and
Eighty One</TIMEX> before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, the subscriber, personally appeared <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah Down</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Jeremiah Donovan</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Olean</ENAMEX> in
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> known to be the same person described in and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the within
and <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">mother</ENAMEX> and an alknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX> scouted the same on a private examination by <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, apart from <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX>, acknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">she</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">he</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX>,
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">A.T. Eaton</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Notary Public</ENAMEX>.

</SBODY>
</NBX>
